  "prompt": "I won a bet with my best buddy. What should I make him do that's fun?",
  "response": "Okay, to give you the best ideas, I need a little more information!  But here are some general ideas broken down by category, and then some questions to help me narrow it down:\n\n**General Fun Ideas (adaptable to many situations):**\n\n*   **Embarrassing Public Performance:**\n    *   **Karaoke Choice:** Force him to sing a ridiculously embarrassing song (think \"Baby\" by Justin Bieber, or a very cheesy 80s ballad).\n    *   **Public Serenade:** He has to serenade a stranger (with your permission, of course!).\n    *   **Silly Outfit Day:** He has to wear a ridiculously silly outfit of your choosing for the entire day. The more ridiculous, the better.\n\n*   **Food/Drink Related:**\n    *   **Mystery Food Challenge:** Blindfold him and make him try a series of weird and interesting foods. Bonus points if you film his reactions!\n    *   **Cook a Meal:** He has to cook you a fancy, multi-course meal. Even better if he's not a good cook!\n    *   **Bartender for the Night:** If you're of age, he has to be your bartender for the night, making all your drinks (even the complicated ones!).\n    *   **Taste Test Challenge:** You get to pick a series of very similar foods (like different brands of cola, or hot sauces) and he has to try them all and identify them correctly.\n\n*   **Skill-Based Challenges:**\n    *   **Learn a New Skill:** He has to learn a silly new skill in a short amount of time, like juggling, doing a magic trick, or making balloon animals. He then has to perform it for you.\n    *   **Video Game Challenge:** Pick a video game he's terrible at and make him play it for a certain amount of time.\n\n*   **Acts of Service/Friendship:**\n    *   **Do Chores:** He has to do your least favorite chore for a month (e.g., laundry, dishes, cleaning the bathroom).\n    *   **Be Your Assistant:** He has to be your personal assistant for a day, running errands and doing whatever you need (within reason, of course!).\n    *   **Plan a Fun Outing:** He has to plan a fun and exciting outing for the both of you.\n\n**Before I can give you more tailored ideas, tell me:**\n\n*   **What kind of bet was it?** (This might give clues about his strengths/weaknesses to exploit)\n*   **What are your/his senses of humor like?** (Is he okay with public humiliation, or is he more sensitive?)\n*   **What's your budget?** (Some ideas might cost money.)\n*   **How much time do you have?** (Some ideas take longer than others.)\n*   **Are there any limits?** (Anything he's absolutely not willing to do?)\n*   **Are there any shared interests?** (This will help you find a task that will be enjoyable for both of you)\n\nOnce I have this info, I can give you some truly hilarious and personalized ideas!",
